{{Use dmy dates|date=December 2017}} {{Infobox holiday |holiday_name = Father-Daughter Day |significance = Honoring relationships of fathers and daughters |frequency = Annual |firsttime = 2017 |observedby = United States |date = Second Sunday in October |type = National |week_ordinal = second |weekday = Sunday |month = October |scheduling = nth weekday of the month |relatedto = In history and celebrations: [[Father's Day]], [[Mother's Day]], [[Parents' Day]], [[National Grandparents Day]], [[Siblings Day]] }}
'''Father-Daughter Day''' (sometimes called '''National Father-Daughter Day''') is a holiday recognized annually on the second Sunday of October in the United States, honoring the relationship between a father and a daughter.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://2017chasescalendarofevents.com/index.php|title=2017 CHASE'S Calendar of Events|website=2017chasescalendarofevents.com}}</ref> Unlike [[Mother's Day]] and [[Father's Day]], it is not federally recognized.
==History== The U.S. holiday was originally conceived by [[Smokey Robinson]] to honor his relationship with his six daughters. In human development the relationship between fathers and sons overshadows the bond with daughters. This holiday promotes the development of young women through their father.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://primarywave.com/smokey-robinson-announces-the-launch-of-father-daughter-day-on-october-8th/|title=Smokey Robinson Announces The Launch Of Father Daughter Day on October 8th – Primary Wave|website=primarywave.com}}</ref>
Robinson stated: “There are many different kinds of families today, and we know that all parental relationships are important to the healthy development of children, but the father/daughter bond is unique and one that is near to my heart. The father/daughter relationship shapes a young woman’s perspective of men and what to expect from them. I believe that female empowerment begins in the home and fathers must set a healthy example through their personal actions and interactions.”
===Celebration=== Examples of commemoration during Father-Daughter Day can be both commercial or intangible. Nonmaterial examples of observances during this day include embracing one another with hugs, spending quality time together, and honoring their presence in your life.
In September 2017, [[Rockabye Baby!|Rockabye Baby! Music]] released a [[lullaby]] version of Smokey Robinson's "[[My Girl (The Temptations song)|My Girl]]" to support the holiday.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.rockabyebabymusic.com/collections/music/products/lullaby-rendition-of-temptations-my-girl|title=Lullaby Rendition of Temptations' "My Girl"|website=Rockabye Baby!}}</ref> In October 2017, greeting card company [[American Greetings]] announced their plan to release a line of eCards with Smokey Robinson to celebrate the launch of Father-Daughter Day.<ref>{{cite web|url=https://www.americangreetings.com/ecards/smokey-robinson|title=Smokey Robinson's songs are now ecards!|website=AmericanGreetings.com}}</ref>
==Father absence in the United States== {{main article|Father absence}}
Fifteen million U.S. children live without a father.<ref>{{cite web|url=http://www.washingtontimes.com/news/2012/dec/25/fathers-disappear-from-households-across-america/|title=Fathers disappear from households across America|first=The Washington Times|last=http://www.washingtontimes.com|publisher=}}</ref> While father absence mainly results from parental divorce and separation,<ref name=":0">{{Cite journal|last=Amato|first=Paul R.|date=1 June 2010|title=Research on Divorce: Continuing Trends and New Developments|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1111/j.1741-3737.2010.00723.x/abstract|journal=Journal of Marriage and Family|language=en|volume=72|issue=3|pages=650–666|doi=10.1111/j.1741-3737.2010.00723.x|issn=1741-3737}}</ref><ref>{{Cite journal|last=McLanahan|first=Sara|last2=Tach|first2=Laura|last3=Schneider|first3=Daniel|date=1 January 2013|title=The Causal Effects of Father Absence|url=https://dx.doi.org/10.1146/annurev-soc-071312-145704|journal=Annual Review of Sociology|volume=39|issue=1|pages=399–427|doi=10.1146/annurev-soc-071312-145704|pmc=3904543|pmid=24489431}}</ref> other factors such as family poverty, developmental difficulties have been associated with father absence, the effects of which have been explained by various theoretical approaches. Fathers are traditionally deemed a provider of protection and support for the child's development.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Draper|first=Patricia|last2=Harpending|first2=Henry|date=1 January 1982|title=Father Absence and Reproductive Strategy: An Evolutionary Perspective|jstor=3629848|journal=Journal of Anthropological Research|volume=38|issue=3|pages=255–273|doi=10.1086/jar.38.3.3629848}}</ref> Early maturing girls have been found to be at risk for teenage pregnancy,<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Udry|first=J. Richard|last2=Cliquet|first2=R. L.|date=1 February 1982|title=A cross-cultural examination of the relationship between ages at menarche, marriage, and first birth|url=https://link.springer.com/article/10.2307/2061128|journal=Demography|language=en|volume=19|issue=1|pages=53–63|doi=10.2307/2061128|issn=0070-3370}}</ref> drinking<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Mezzich|first=A|title=Substance use and risky sexual behavior in female adolescents|url=http://linkinghub.elsevier.com/retrieve/pii/S0376871696013336|journal=Drug and Alcohol Dependence|volume=44|issue=2–3|pages=157–166|doi=10.1016/s0376-8716(96)01333-6}}</ref> and weight problems,<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Ness|first=Roberta|date=1 January 1991|title=Adiposity and age of menarche in Hispanic women|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/ajhb.1310030108/abstract|journal=American Journal of Human Biology|language=en|volume=3|issue=1|pages=41–47|doi=10.1002/ajhb.1310030108|issn=1520-6300}}</ref><ref name=":5">{{Cite journal|last=Wellens|first=R.|last2=Malina|first2=R. M.|last3=Roche|first3=A. F.|last4=Chumlea|first4=W. C.|last5=Guo|first5=S.|last6=Siervogel|first6=R. M.|date=1 January 1992|title=Body size and fatness in young adults in relation to age at menarche|url=http://onlinelibrary.wiley.com/doi/10.1002/ajhb.1310040610/abstract|journal=American Journal of Human Biology|language=en|volume=4|issue=6|pages=783–787|doi=10.1002/ajhb.1310040610|issn=1520-6300}}</ref> and giving birth to low birth weight infants.<ref>{{Cite journal|last=Scholl|first=Theresa|last2=Hediger|first2=Mary|last3=Vasilenko|first3=Peter|last4=Ances|first4=Isadore|last5=Smith|first5=Woolcott|last6=Salmon|first6=Ruth|date=1 January 1989|title=Effects of early maturation on fetal growth|url=https://dx.doi.org/10.1080/03014468900000462|journal=Annals of Human Biology|volume=16|issue=4|pages=335–345|doi=10.1080/03014468900000462|issn=0301-4460}}</ref>
